Pumpkin Skillet Lasagna
  --Deborah Murphy

1 tbsp olive oil 
1/2 yellow onion, chopped
3 cloves garlic, minced
1/4 tsp red pepper flakes
2 tsp chopped fresh sage
1 tsp chopped fresh thyme
15 oz can pumpkin puree
3 c vegetable broth 
1/2 tsp sea salt  
9 lasagna noodles, broken into bite sized pieces
15 oz can white beans, drained and rinsed
1/2 c vegan ricotta cheese
4 tbsp vegan parmesan
1 c vegan shredded mozzarella

Heat a large 12" oven safe, nonstick skillet with a fitted lid over high heat. Add the olive oil and onion to the skillet. Saute until softened and translucent, ~3-4 minu. Add the garlic, sage and thyme and stir to combine. Cook until fragrant, ~1 min. Add the pumpkin puree, broth, and salt to the skillet, stir to combine, and bring to a simmer. Add the pasta to the skillet, stir to combine.
Reduce the heat to medium, simmer covered, making sure the noodles are submerged in the liquid). Stir occasionally so that the noodles don’t stick to each other or the bottom of the skillet. Cook until the pasta is just tender and the sauce has thickened, ~13-15 min. Remove from heat and stir in the white beans, ricotta cheese and 2 tbsp of the parmesan. Top with the shredded mozzarella and remaining 2 tbsp of parmesan cheese. Transfer to the broiler on the second rack from the top and broil on high until the cheese is melted and slightly browned on top, 2-3 min. Garnish with parsley and fresh thyme and serve.
